|title=List of Area Codes |publisher=Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications |accessdate=13 December 2018}}</ref> | registration_plate = Hamamatsu | footnotes = }} Located on the northeast shore of {{ill|Lake Hamana|ja|浜名湖|12=draft}} and featuring Uchūra Bay between Kanzanji-chō and Kusamatsu-chō, Kanzanji serves as a hub for tourism in the Hamamatsu and Lake Hamana area. The {{ill|Kanzanji Onsen Lantern Floating Fireworks Festival|ja|舘山寺温泉灯篭流し花火大会|12=draft}} is held here every summer. In 2004, the {{ill|Lake Hamana Expo|ja|浜名湖花博|12=draft}} was hosted in nearby Murakushi-chō, further enhancing its appeal as a tourist center.
