== Notes == [[File:Kanzan Ji Keshiki cropped Totomi Koseki Zue Frame 12.jpg|thumb|200px|An Edo-period reference to "館山寺" in {{ill|Totomi Koseki Zue|ja|遠江古蹟図会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Totomi Koseki Zue|qq=}} (edited by Fuji Chōkō, 1803, National Diet Library Collection)]] When written in kanji, Kanzanji-chō is officially rendered with the common character "舘." However, alternative renderings using the standard "館" are often seen, including on signage for the Hamamatsu Nishi Interchange and Kanzanji Bus Stop on the Tōmei Expressway.<ref>Koike, Kazuo. ''The World of Variant Kanji Characters''. Kawade Shobō Shinsha, 2013, p. 117.</ref><ref>Hamamatsu City Office, "[https://www.city.hamamatsu.shizuoka.jp/shiminkyodo/intro/dmc/kuwari/zentyoumei1.html Neighborhood Name and Postal Code List]" (2020-01-01).</ref>
