 web|ja|url=https://www.soumu.go.jp/main_sosiki/joho_tsusin/top/tel_number/shigai_list.html |title=List of Area Codes |publisher=Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications |accessdate=13 December 2018}}</ref> | registration_plate = Hamamatsu | footnotes = }} Located on the northeast shore of [[:en:Lake Hamana|Lake Hamana]] and featuring Uchūra Bay between Kanzanji-chō and Kusamatsu-chō, Kanzanji serves as a hub for tourism in the Hamamatsu and Lake Hamana area. The {{ill|Kanzanji Onsen Lantern Floating Fireworks Festival|ja|舘山寺温泉灯篭流し花火大会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanzanji Onsen Lantern Floating Fireworks Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 浜名湖かんざんじ温泉灯篭流し花火大会}} is held here every summer. In 2004, the {{ill|Lake Hamana Expo|ja|浜名湖花博|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake Hamana Expo|qq=}} was hosted in nearby Murakushi-chō, further enhancing its appeal as a tourist center.
