== Kanzanji == {{Infobox temple | name = Kanzanji | image = Kanzanji 20210102.jpg | image_size = 300px | caption = Main hall | address = Kanzanji-cho 2231, Chūō-ku, Hamamatsu City, Shizuoka Prefecture<ref name="index" /> | location = | latd = 34 | latm = 45 | lats = 40 | longd = 137 | longm = 36 | longs = 48 | sango = Akihasan<ref name="index" /> | inno = | sect = Sōtō-shū<ref name="index" /> | affiliation = | temple_Rank = | honzon = Kokūzō Bosatsu (Ākāśagarbha)<ref name="honzon" /><ref name="kotoba_daiji" /> | founded = 810 CE<ref name="index" /> | founder = Kūkai<ref name="index" /> | restoration_year = | restorer = | full_name = Sōtō-shū Akihasan Kanzanji<ref name="index" /> | aliases = | pilg_route = Hamanako Coast 88 Kannon Pilgrimage, 27th Temple<ref name="index" /><ref name="koganreijo">{{Cite web|ja|url=https://nippon-reijo.jimdofree.com/%E6%8E%B2%E8%BC%89%E9%9C%8A%E5%A0%B4%E3%81%AE%E4%B8%80%E8%A6%A7/%E5%BC%98%E6%B3%95%E5%A4%A7%E5%B8%AB%E9%9C%8A%E5%A0%B4/%E6%B5%9C%E5%90%8D%E6%B9%96%E5%B2%B8%E5%85%AB%E5%8D%81%E5%85%AB%E3%83%B6%E6%89%80%E9%9C%8A%E5%A0%B4/ |title=Hamanako Coast Shikoku 88 Pilgrimage |publisher=Nippon Pilgrimage |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref> | cultural_assets = | website = [http://kanzanji.net/ Kanzanji Official Website] | map = Japan Shizuoka | map2 = }} == Overview == The temple is said to have been founded by [[:en:Kūkai|Kūkai]] (Kōbō Daishi) in 810 CE, making it a historically significant temple. It was originally a sub-temple of [[:en:Akihasan Hongū Akiha Shrine|Akihasan Hongū Akiha Shrine]].<ref name="index">{{Cite web|ja|url=http://kanzanji.net/index.html |title=Sōtō-shū Akihasan Kanzanji |publisher=Official Website |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref> The temple also houses a shrine to [[:en:Atago Shrine (Kyoto)|Atago Shrine (disambiguation)]].<ref name="jinjacho">{{Cite web|ja|url=http://www.shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4414226 |title=Atago Shrine |publisher=Shizuoka Shrine Association |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref>
Its [[:en:Honzon|Honzon]] is [[:en:Ākāśagarbha|Kokūzō Bosatsu]].<ref name="honzon">{{Cite web|ja|url=http://kanzanji.net/gohonzon.html |title=About the Honzon |publisher=Official Website |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref><ref name="kotoba_daiji">{{Cite Kotobank|word=Kanzanji |encyclopedia=Digital Daijisen Plus |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref> The shrine enshrines {{ill|Akiba Gongen|ja|秋葉権現|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akiha Gongen|qq=}} (Akiha Sanshaku Bō Daigongen) as its guardian deity.<ref name="honzon" /> A fire festival is held annually on 15 December, where fire-walking follows sutra recitations.<ref name="himatsuri">{{Cite web|ja|url=http://kanzanji.net/akihasan.html#himatsuri |title=What is Akihasan Faith? |publisher=Official Website |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref> General participants are also welcome to join the fire-walking.<ref name="himatsuri" /> The temple preserves a letter addressed to [[:en:Ikkyū|Ikkyū Sōjun]] from his mother.<ref name="honzon" />
=== History === * '''810 CE (Kōnin 1):''' Founded by Kūkai as a [[:en:Shingon Buddhism|Shingon-shū]] temple.<ref name="index" /> * '''1187 CE (Bunji 3):''' Destroyed by fire during wartime. Subsequently rebuilt by [[:en:Minamoto no Yoritomo|Minamoto no Yoritomo]].<ref name="index" /> * '''1384 CE (Genchū 1):''' Destroyed again by fire during wartime.<ref name="index" /> * '''1362 CE (Jōji 1):''' Fujiwara no Motohide (later Ōsawa clan) arrived as the lord of Horie Castle, providing patronage as the castle’s prayer temple.<ref name="index" /> * '''1598 CE (Keichō 3):''' Received shuin (vermilion seal) land grant from [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]].<ref name="index" /> * '''1870 CE (Meiji 3):''' Abolished due to the {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri|ja|神仏分離令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbutsu Bunri|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 神仏分離|1=shinbutsu bunri|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1970535}} and [[:en:Haibutsu kishaku|Haibutsu kishaku]] policies.<ref name="index" /> * '''1890 CE (Meiji 23):''' Restored by inviting Priest Maki Taizen of Akihasan Akihaji. Converted to Sōtō-shū and renamed its mountain title from Chūreizan to Akihasan.<ref name="index" />
=== Kanzan === The temple and the adjacent Atago Shrine are located at the end of the onsen street, accessible via stairs. Behind these lies the low mountain {{ill|Kanzan|ja|舘山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanzan|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, which faces [[:en:Lake Hamana|Lake Hamana]] and features a promenade with various landmarks.<ref name="sansaku">{{Cite web|ja|url=http://kanzanji.net/sansaku.html |title=Kanzan Walks |publisher=Official Website |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref><ref name="kanko_map">{{Cite web|ja|url=https://www.kanzanji.gr.jp/wp-content/themes/kanzanji/img/map/map_2021_spring.pdf |format=pdf |title=Kanzanji Onsen Stroll Map |publisher=[https://www.kanzanji.gr.jp/ Kanzanji Onsen Tourism Association] |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref> * Anadai-shi<ref name="honzon" /><ref name="sansaku" /> * Enmusubi Jizō-son<ref name="honzon" /><ref name="sansaku" /> * Sei Kannon Bosatsu (Kanzanji Great Kannon)<ref name="honzon" /><ref name="sansaku" /> * Saigyō Rock<ref name="sansaku" /> * Tosaka Rock<ref name="sansaku" /> * Fujimi Rock<ref name="sansaku" /> * Observation Deck<ref name="sansaku" />
=== Access === * '''By Car:''' 15 minutes from {{ill|Hamamatsu Nishi Interchange|ja|浜松西インターチェンジ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamamatsu Nishi Interchange|qq=|1=Hamamatsu-nishi interchange|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11557882}} on the [[:en:Tōmei Expressway|Tōmei Expressway]], or closer via Kanzanji Smart Interchange.<ref name="access">{{Cite web|ja|url=http://kanzanji.net/access.html |title=Transport & Access |publisher=Official Website |accessdate=22 April 2021}}</ref> * '''By Bus:''' About 45 minutes from [[:en:Hamamatsu Station|Hamamatsu Station]] on Entetsu Bus; alight at "Kanzanji Onsen" stop and walk 5 minutes.<ref name="access" />
=== Gallery === <gallery> File:Kanzanji atagojinja 20210102.jpg|Atago Shrine within the temple grounds File:Kanzanji atagojinja torii 20210102.jpg|Atago Shrine torii. The stairs leading to Kanzanji's main hall are to the right. File:Kanzanji Seikannon Bosatsu 01.JPG|Sei Kannon Bosatsu (built in 1937<ref name="sansaku" />), likened to former Prime Minister [[:en:Shinzo Abe|Shinzō Abe]] by some media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chunichi.co.jp/article/113570 |title="Looks just like him": Abe Shinzō and Kanzanji Kannon Statue |publisher=Chunichi Shimbun |date=1 September 2020 |accessdate=6 September 2020}}</ref> </gallery>
== Kanzanji-chō == {{Pathnav|Japan|Shizuoka Prefecture|Hamamatsu City|Chūō-ku|'''Kanzanji-chō'''|hide=1|frame=1}} {{Infobox settlement | name = Kanzanji-chō | settlement_type = Town | image_skyline = Kanzanji-hotspring-town.jpg | imagesize = 300px | image_caption = Kanzanji Onsen district | image_map = | map_caption = Location of Kanzanji-chō | pushpin_map = Japan Shizuoka | latd = 34 | latm = 45 | lats = 39.69 | latNS = N | longd = 137 | longm = 36 | longs = 48.26 | longEW = E | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{flagicon|JPN}} Japan | subdivision_type1 = Prefecture | subdivision_name1 = {{flagicon|Shizuoka Prefecture}} Shizuoka Prefecture | subdivision_type2 = City | subdivision_name2 = {{flagicon|Hamamatsu City}} Hamamatsu City | subdivision_type3 = Ward | subdivision_name3 = {{ill|Chūō-ku, Hamamatsu|ja|Chūō-ku, Hamamatsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chūō-ku, Hamamatsu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} | established_title1 = Established | established_date1 = | area_footnotes = <ref name="menseki">{{PDFlink|[https://www.city.hamamatsu.shizuoka.jp/gyousei/library/3_tochi-kisyou/documents/27-2_menseki-jinkou_area_kubetsu.pdf Land Statistics: Neighborhood Area Sizes (March 2010) - Hamamatsu City] |accessdate=14 December 2018}}</ref> | area_total_km2 = 2.2506 | population_as_of = 1 December 2018 | population_footnotes = <ref name="population">{{Cite web|ja|url=https://www.city.hamamatsu.shizuoka.jp/gyousei/library/1_jinkou-setai/005_kubetsu.html |title=Population Statistics by Neighborhood |publisher=Hamamatsu City |accessdate=13 December 2018}}</ref> | population_total = 2542 | population_density_km2 = auto | timezone1 = JST | utc_offset1 = +9 | postal_code_type = Postal Code | postal_code = 431-1209<ref name="postal">{{Cite web|ja|url=https://www.post.japanpost.jp/cgi-zip/zipcode.php?zip=4311209 |title=Postal Code |publisher=Japan Post |accessdate=13 December 2018}}</ref> | area_code = 053 (Hamamatsu MA)<ref name="areacode">{{Cite web|ja|url=https://www.soumu.go.jp/main_sosiki/joho_tsusin/top/tel_number/shigai_list.html |title=List of Area Codes |publisher=Ministry of Internal Affairs and Communications |accessdate=13 December 2018}}</ref> | registration_plate = Hamamatsu | footnotes = }} Located on the northeast shore of [[:en:Lake Hamana|Lake Hamana]] and featuring Uchūra Bay between Kanzanji-chō and Kusamatsu-chō, Kanzanji serves as a hub for tourism in the Hamamatsu and Lake Hamana area. The {{ill|Kanzanji Onsen Lantern Floating Fireworks Festival|ja|舘山寺温泉灯篭流し花火大会|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanzanji Onsen Lantern Floating Fireworks Festival|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 浜名湖かんざんじ温泉灯篭流し花火大会|1=Kanzanji Onsen Lantern Floating Fireworks Festival|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q85881965}} is held here every summer. In 2004, the {{ill|Lake Hamana Expo|ja|浜名湖花博|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake Hamana Expo|qq=|1=Pacific Flora 2004|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11557606}} was hosted in nearby Murakushi-chō, further enhancing its appeal as a tourist center.
=== Kanzanji Onsen === The {{ill|Kanzanji Onsen|ja|舘山寺温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanzanji Onsen|qq=|1=Kanzanji Onsen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11613539}} was discovered in 1958 and is known for its therapeutic effects on fatigue, neuralgia, and poor circulation.
=== Facilities and Attractions === {{see also|Kanzanji Onsen}} * [[:en:Kanzanji Ropeway|Kanzanji Ropeway]] * {{ill|Hamamatsu City Zoo|ja|浜松市動物園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamamatsu City Zoo|qq=|1=Hamamatsu Zoological Gardens|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11557788}} * {{ill|Hamamatsu City Flower Park|ja|浜松市フラワーパーク|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamamatsu City Flower Park|qq=|1=Hamamatsu Flower Park|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9055804}} * {{ill|Hamanako Kanzanji Art Museum|ja|浜名湖舘山寺美術博物館|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamanako Kanzanji Art Museum|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} * {{ill|Hamanako Music Box Museum|ja|浜名湖オルゴールミュージアム|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamanako Music Box Museum|qq=|1=Hamanako Orgel Museum|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11557595}} (in Kusamatsu-chō) * {{ill|Hamanako Pal Pal|ja|浜名湖パルパル|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hamanako Pal Pal|qq=|1=Hamanako Palpal|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11557598}}
